summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 19217, entitled "An Ordinance granting N. R. Sibley, a resident of Seattle, King County, Washington, his successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, acquire, operate and maintain a refrigerating and cold storage plant, pipes, mains and appurtenances for the purpose of manufacturing, selling and supplying means of refrigeration to the citizens of Seattle, King County, State of Washington, and defining the rights, privileges and powers thereunder," approved September 26, 1908.
